1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,200
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:02,500
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:05,533
(Episode 48)

4
00:00:08,896 --> 00:00:12,208
Isn't this the place we came
with the Chairman last time?

5
00:00:12,521 --> 00:00:13,521
You're right.

6
00:00:14,315 --> 00:00:16,473
Is this really the address Gyeol sent?

7
00:00:17,188 --> 00:00:18,717
Yes. This is it.

8
00:00:19,877 --> 00:00:22,477
Well, look who it is.

9
00:00:23,098 --> 00:00:24,600
Hello.

10
00:00:25,457 --> 00:00:27,307
What brings you here?

11
00:00:28,543 --> 00:00:31,333
Here for some bindaetteok again?

12
00:00:32,137 --> 00:00:34,637
No, not this time.

13
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:36,712
Where exactly is this?

14
00:00:38,279 --> 00:00:40,472
This is Eun Hyeong's house.

15
00:00:41,298 --> 00:00:44,909
It's the address
of the real estate office?

16
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:47,608
Yes, 9 Jeongdam-ro 4-gil.

17
00:00:47,608 --> 00:00:49,259
It's inside the real estate office.

18
00:00:49,868 --> 00:00:51,488
What brings you here?

19
00:00:56,028 --> 00:00:58,907
Ma'am, what brings you here?

20
00:01:00,091 --> 00:01:01,552
Then this is...

21
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:05,899
Is my grandson renting a room
in your house?

22
00:01:06,571 --> 00:01:08,020
Yes, that's right.

23
00:01:08,020 --> 00:01:11,261
What? Gyeol is living at Mr. Cho's house?

24
00:01:12,028 --> 00:01:15,581
Is Eun Ae's Team Manager your grandson?

25
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:19,288
Don't just stand out here.
Please come inside.

26
00:01:20,213 --> 00:01:21,213
Okay.

27
00:01:25,385 --> 00:01:27,944
I never thought...

28
00:01:28,203 --> 00:01:30,208
Gyeol would be living in this house.

29
00:01:30,577 --> 00:01:32,299
It's a small world, isn't it?

30
00:01:33,036 --> 00:01:35,095
I should've told you sooner,

31
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:38,811
but Team Manager Ko told my husband...

32
00:01:39,101 --> 00:01:42,336
not to tell his parents, so we couldn't.

33
00:01:43,279 --> 00:01:44,579
I understand.

34
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:49,621
When I heard he even eats breakfast
and dinner with the landlord's family,

35
00:01:50,373 --> 00:01:52,673
I wondered what kind of family
he'd ended up with.

36
00:01:53,385 --> 00:01:56,744
Now that I know it's your family,
I feel much more at ease.

37
00:01:56,997 --> 00:01:59,973
We just set out one more spoon
at the table when we eat.

38
00:02:00,268 --> 00:02:02,653
We're not doing anything special for him.

39
00:02:04,063 --> 00:02:06,629
By the way, why did you bring all this?

40
00:02:07,860 --> 00:02:10,181
It's just some kimchi
and a few side dishes.

41
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,555
I felt like we've been imposing too much.

42
00:02:12,942 --> 00:02:14,325
Imposing?

43
00:02:15,042 --> 00:02:18,149
We charge him rent and meal expenses.

44
00:02:19,027 --> 00:02:21,517
Right, are you fully recovered now?

45
00:02:21,517 --> 00:02:25,179
Yes. After eating the soup
you made for me that day,

46
00:02:25,179 --> 00:02:26,731
I got my strength back.

47
00:02:27,093 --> 00:02:28,529
Thank you so much.

48
00:02:28,529 --> 00:02:30,421
Don't mention it.

49
00:02:31,001 --> 00:02:33,268
I'm glad you're feeling better.

50
00:02:34,013 --> 00:02:37,753
I almost forgot. I heard your daughter...

51
00:02:37,753 --> 00:02:39,568
works on the same team as Gyeol.

52
00:02:40,666 --> 00:02:42,472
Do you know Eun Ae?

53
00:02:42,472 --> 00:02:46,107
Yes. Long before we met,

54
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:49,571
there was a time
I almost collapsed on the street,

55
00:02:50,492 --> 00:02:52,368
and your daughter helped me then.

56
00:02:53,979 --> 00:02:57,021
I also saw her once
when my husband was in the hospital.

57
00:02:58,053 --> 00:03:01,393
When I heard from Gyeol
that they worked on the same team,

58
00:03:01,393 --> 00:03:03,346
I was so happy.

59
00:03:03,346 --> 00:03:05,025
What an incredible coincidence.

60
00:03:05,025 --> 00:03:06,025
I know.

61
00:03:09,232 --> 00:03:12,037
His room is upstairs.
Would you like to take a look...

62
00:03:12,037 --> 00:03:13,315
since you've come all this way?

63
00:03:13,315 --> 00:03:15,968
Should I? Gyeol did tell me...

64
00:03:15,968 --> 00:03:18,544
- to check out his room.
- Sure.

65
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:21,199
Okay.

66
00:03:26,449 --> 00:03:27,768
Thank you for the food.

67
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:32,392
By the way, I heard that Team Manager
renting a room here...

68
00:03:32,392 --> 00:03:35,757
is from the Kangsu Group family.

69
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:37,651
Yes, that's right.

70
00:03:37,899 --> 00:03:40,544
He's Chairman Kang's second grandson.

71
00:03:41,307 --> 00:03:43,939
Then that elderly gentleman
who came here before...

72
00:03:43,939 --> 00:03:46,192
He's the chairman of Kangsu Group.

73
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:49,869
I thought he was the chairman
of some seniors' association.

74
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:52,443
A seniors' association? Come on.

75
00:03:53,083 --> 00:03:55,405
To tell you about Chairman Ko Kang Su,

76
00:03:55,616 --> 00:03:57,427
on April 10, 1980,

77
00:03:57,427 --> 00:03:58,627
- he founded Kangsu Construction...
- Grandma.

78
00:03:59,837 --> 00:04:01,420
I'll go pick up Bit Na.

79
00:04:01,420 --> 00:04:05,240
Okay. Yeon Ja has guests over,
so go on and come right back.

80
00:04:06,297 --> 00:04:07,297
But...

81
00:04:08,292 --> 00:04:10,992
Why are you all dressed up
just to go pick up Bit Na?

82
00:04:11,624 --> 00:04:14,273
Bit Na hasn't looked
very energetic lately.

83
00:04:14,273 --> 00:04:17,552
I thought she might feel better
if her pretty aunt showed up.

84
00:04:18,168 --> 00:04:20,269
Ta-da! Here's hoping it works.

85
00:04:21,195 --> 00:04:23,576
I'll text Eun Ae's mother
and let her know I'm picking up Bit Na.

86
00:04:24,152 --> 00:04:25,824
- I'll be back.
- Okay.

87
00:04:31,493 --> 00:04:35,243
That's strange.
Where have I seen her before?

88
00:04:38,465 --> 00:04:40,213
The room is pretty small, isn't it?

89
00:04:41,176 --> 00:04:43,529
Leaving a large, nice room
at the chairman's house...

90
00:04:43,529 --> 00:04:45,533
to move into a place like this...

91
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:46,960
No.

92
00:04:47,747 --> 00:04:51,272
This whole house feels warm and bright.

93
00:04:52,481 --> 00:04:54,109
Now I understand
why Gyeol looked even better...

94
00:04:55,114 --> 00:04:57,755
after moving out of the family home.

95
00:04:58,377 --> 00:04:59,377
Not at all.

96
00:05:04,784 --> 00:05:06,419
Please make yourself comfortable here.

97
00:05:06,651 --> 00:05:08,933
It's almost time to pick up
my granddaughter from kindergarten.

98
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:10,333
I need to go out for a bit.

99
00:05:10,596 --> 00:05:12,829
No, I should get going too.

100
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:16,379
I'll come back another time
when my grandson is here.

101
00:05:16,628 --> 00:05:19,187
Why don't you stay until he gets off work?

102
00:05:19,436 --> 00:05:23,280
I think it'd be nice if you saw him
and had a meal together.

103
00:05:23,488 --> 00:05:24,811
I'll do that next time.

104
00:05:26,522 --> 00:05:28,187
- Will you?
- Yes.

105
00:05:35,685 --> 00:05:37,352
One, two, back rock.

106
00:05:37,352 --> 00:05:40,152
One, two, back rock. One, two.

107
00:05:40,981 --> 00:05:44,516
Back rock. One, two, back rock. One, two.

108
00:05:44,516 --> 00:05:46,187
Back rock. One, two.

109
00:05:47,841 --> 00:05:49,232
Ma'am,

110
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:52,248
have we really never met before?

111
00:05:52,248 --> 00:05:53,728
I told you we haven't.

112
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:57,376
We're complete strangers,
so why do you keep talking nonsense?

113
00:05:57,376 --> 00:05:59,276
Okay, I'm sorry.

114
00:06:06,392 --> 00:06:09,259
One, two, three, and...

115
00:06:19,362 --> 00:06:20,362
At the lobby...

116
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:24,579
What the heck?
Are you trying to hit on me right now?

117
00:06:25,420 --> 00:06:29,520
Are you asking for a beating?

118
00:06:31,973 --> 00:06:33,401
Are you done talking?

119
00:06:33,401 --> 00:06:36,341
Yes.
Please continue looking after my grandson.

120
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,968
There's no need to ask me.

121
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,920
They say that as people age,

122
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:46,437
their whole life shows on their face.

123
00:06:47,011 --> 00:06:49,640
But I don't see any trace
of life's hardships on yours.

124
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:53,397
You look like you've walked nothing
but flower-lined roads.

125
00:06:54,087 --> 00:06:55,555
Come on.

126
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,605
Fate really is...

127
00:06:59,624 --> 00:07:00,624
Sorry?

128
00:07:00,965 --> 00:07:01,965
Well...

129
00:07:02,636 --> 00:07:05,552
Fate is such a mysterious thing.

130
00:07:05,952 --> 00:07:07,816
That's all I meant.

131
00:07:08,224 --> 00:07:11,600
I should go pick up my granddaughter now.
Take care.

132
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,667
No,
Cho Rong already went to pick up Bit Na.

133
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:16,230
She said she'd text you.

134
00:07:16,230 --> 00:07:17,389
Really?

135
00:07:18,983 --> 00:07:20,557
I haven't checked...

136
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,664
You're right.

137
00:07:22,664 --> 00:07:23,664
I almost forgot.

138
00:07:23,784 --> 00:07:26,299
My husband loves the bindaetteok here.

139
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,971
Could I get some to go?

140
00:07:27,971 --> 00:07:29,483
Of course.

141
00:07:30,171 --> 00:07:31,571
Just wait a little.

142
00:07:31,771 --> 00:07:34,587
I'll make you a special batch
fresh off the griddle.

143
00:07:36,544 --> 00:07:37,544
Hello?

144
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:40,688
Yes, long-term rentals
are hard to find these days.

145
00:07:41,501 --> 00:07:45,277
You're coming now? Okay, I'll wait.

146
00:07:45,987 --> 00:07:47,559
I have a customer coming.

147
00:07:47,559 --> 00:07:49,421
Then you should get going.

148
00:07:49,947 --> 00:07:52,699
Please come back
when your grandson is here.

149
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,864
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

150
00:08:01,862 --> 00:08:04,499
So, did you talk to your daughter?

151
00:08:04,856 --> 00:08:07,981
She's got a thing going on
with Team Manager Ko, right?

152
00:08:08,711 --> 00:08:10,261
I don't think they're dating yet.

153
00:08:10,722 --> 00:08:11,833
What are you talking about?

154
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:14,821
I guarantee you those two are dating.

155
00:08:15,006 --> 00:08:16,360
I'm telling you, it's obvious.

156
00:08:16,687 --> 00:08:18,669
How can you be so sure?

157
00:08:19,808 --> 00:08:23,036
I told you
I saw them eating lunch together before.

158
00:08:23,036 --> 00:08:24,163
I was shocked.

159
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:28,363
Gyeol has never opened his heart
to anyone before.

160
00:08:30,103 --> 00:08:31,503
Anyway, it's a fact.

161
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,087
Are you okay with it, sir?

162
00:08:35,555 --> 00:08:36,555
With what?

163
00:08:36,555 --> 00:08:39,771
With my daughter dating your son.

164
00:08:40,335 --> 00:08:42,635
If they are, then they are.
What's the problem?

165
00:08:43,568 --> 00:08:45,603
I'm not that narrow-minded.

166
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,937
Do you know how free-spirited
and open-minded I am?

167
00:08:48,937 --> 00:08:50,333
Mr. Cho,
can't you tell just by looking at me?

168
00:08:51,104 --> 00:08:54,419
Come on, take a good look.

169
00:08:54,863 --> 00:08:57,363
Look at me. Does this look
like a corporate CEO's fashion?

170
00:08:57,867 --> 00:09:00,300
With my physique and everything,
I look more like a model or an actor.

171
00:09:01,131 --> 00:09:02,131
Right.

172
00:09:02,538 --> 00:09:04,840
Take a good look around.

173
00:09:05,765 --> 00:09:06,765
See this?

174
00:09:06,765 --> 00:09:09,475
The colorful palette,
the dynamic furniture.

175
00:09:10,168 --> 00:09:12,357
I picked all of it myself.

176
00:09:12,989 --> 00:09:14,122
Good grief.

177
00:09:14,873 --> 00:09:16,747
Did you think I would...

178
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:19,515
oppose them
over some family alliance nonsense?

179
00:09:20,087 --> 00:09:21,619
It's not even Min Ho. Why would I object?

180
00:09:25,552 --> 00:09:27,739
Seriously, I don't care at all.

181
00:09:28,717 --> 00:09:31,856
I told you already.
Gyeol is going back to the U.S. soon.

182
00:09:32,317 --> 00:09:35,299
You think a few months of dating
means marriage?

183
00:09:36,476 --> 00:09:38,776
If they love each other,
that could happen.

184
00:09:39,197 --> 00:09:40,731
Why not?

185
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:42,581
What?

186
00:09:43,447 --> 00:09:45,016
So you're saying...

187
00:09:45,758 --> 00:09:47,723
you and I could become in-laws, Mr. Cho?

188
00:09:54,214 --> 00:09:56,317
Listen, I guarantee it.

189
00:09:56,696 --> 00:10:00,043
That will never happen. So stop dreaming.

190
00:10:00,561 --> 00:10:02,477
Seriously, that's hilarious.

191
00:10:04,211 --> 00:10:06,928
Right.
And what was that thing from before?

192
00:10:07,387 --> 00:10:09,509
Factorial or whatever it was.

193
00:10:09,509 --> 00:10:11,371
You said you could figure out
the password with that.

194
00:10:11,593 --> 00:10:12,593
How do you do it?

195
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:15,664
Why don't you find another way?

196
00:10:16,230 --> 00:10:18,730
Either way, you'll lose your finger.

197
00:10:24,607 --> 00:10:26,387
What? Wait.

198
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,395
Is Cho Seong Jun upset with me?

199
00:10:30,043 --> 00:10:32,675
Because I told him to stop dreaming
about becoming in-laws?

200
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:35,515
That's ridiculous.

201
00:10:39,072 --> 00:10:40,115
Let me carry that. It looks heavy.

202
00:10:40,656 --> 00:10:41,656
I'm fine.

203
00:10:42,269 --> 00:10:45,320
From now on, call me
when you have something heavy to carry.

204
00:10:46,064 --> 00:10:47,429
Why all of a sudden?

205
00:10:47,691 --> 00:10:48,847
Don't you know I'm strong?

206
00:10:48,847 --> 00:10:50,416
Got it, Intern Cho?

207
00:10:51,104 --> 00:10:54,539
And my grandma talked things over
with your mother...

208
00:10:54,539 --> 00:10:56,221
and headed home.

209
00:10:57,030 --> 00:11:00,565
Really? She won't tell
the rest of your family, will she?

210
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:02,833
Don't worry.

211
00:11:03,437 --> 00:11:04,600
Come on. Let's go to the meeting.

212
00:11:04,968 --> 00:11:07,147
- I'll stop by the restroom first.
- Okay.

213
00:11:27,112 --> 00:11:28,112
You look pretty today.

214
00:11:29,228 --> 00:11:32,835
All my usual clothes are in the wash,
so I didn't really have a choice.

215
00:11:34,037 --> 00:11:35,643
It doesn't suit me, right?

216
00:11:37,641 --> 00:11:38,641
What do you mean?

217
00:11:38,641 --> 00:11:41,453
Your outfit practically screams
that you're in love.

218
00:11:42,135 --> 00:11:43,335
How could you not look pretty?

219
00:11:44,313 --> 00:11:45,313
What?

220
00:11:45,565 --> 00:11:46,891
Do you have plans after work?

221
00:11:47,613 --> 00:11:49,581
No, I don't.

222
00:11:49,581 --> 00:11:52,080
Really? Then could you make some time
for me tonight?

223
00:11:55,085 --> 00:11:57,989
Yes, I transferred the membership fee.

224
00:12:00,831 --> 00:12:03,795
My daughter is in the Gold tier?

225
00:12:05,477 --> 00:12:08,141
How many matches can you arrange at most?

226
00:12:09,331 --> 00:12:11,293
Of course I prefer professionals.

227
00:12:11,739 --> 00:12:14,067
As you can see from my daughter's profile,

228
00:12:15,049 --> 00:12:16,355
quality matters more than quantity...

229
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:20,619
No, please make sure
you find someone truly worthy of her.

230
00:12:21,373 --> 00:12:23,652
Yes, thank you.

231
00:12:23,652 --> 00:12:25,357
Wait, what was that about?

232
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:27,964
What's this Gold tier,

233
00:12:27,964 --> 00:12:30,107
and preferred professionals for matching?

234
00:12:30,630 --> 00:12:31,630
You don't need to know.

235
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:36,656
Don't tell me you're trying
to put Seung Ri on the marriage market.

236
00:12:36,656 --> 00:12:38,016
- What?
- That's exactly it.

237
00:12:38,016 --> 00:12:39,632
You're trying to auction off
Seo Seung Ri...

238
00:12:39,632 --> 00:12:42,112
through a matchmaking agency.

239
00:12:42,117 --> 00:12:43,819
Auction her off? What nonsense.

240
00:12:44,075 --> 00:12:45,776
I'm just trying to help her
find a good match.

241
00:12:45,776 --> 00:12:47,691
Then what about Min Ho?
What about Min Ho?

242
00:12:47,691 --> 00:12:48,848
You invited him over before...

243
00:12:49,064 --> 00:12:50,973
and treated him like a son-in-law already.

244
00:12:50,973 --> 00:12:53,661
Min Ho is done. I told you that.

245
00:12:54,363 --> 00:12:56,965
If nothing's happened in ten years,
then it's just a waste of time.

246
00:12:57,701 --> 00:13:00,763
I can't stand watching your sister
suffer anymore.

247
00:13:01,224 --> 00:13:03,232
I'm going to find her a respectable man...

248
00:13:03,232 --> 00:13:05,261
and get her married as soon as possible.

249
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,728
What a traitor.

250
00:13:09,392 --> 00:13:11,887
I'm telling Min Ho
and Seo Seung Ri everything.

251
00:13:11,887 --> 00:13:14,368
Just try running your mouth.

252
00:13:15,184 --> 00:13:18,725
I'll shake you down
and hang you out on the balcony.

253
00:13:20,031 --> 00:13:21,440
How terrifying.

254
00:13:23,027 --> 00:13:25,054
Madam Yu Jeong Ran, who did this to you?

255
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:28,915
Who turned such a delicate, graceful lady
into this?

256
00:13:30,318 --> 00:13:33,037
What? Gyeol is living at Mr. Cho's house?

257
00:13:33,366 --> 00:13:36,605
Yes. As you've probably felt too,

258
00:13:37,431 --> 00:13:40,133
the couple is very kind and warm-hearted.

259
00:13:40,972 --> 00:13:44,019
I think Gyeol has adjusted well there too.

260
00:13:44,845 --> 00:13:47,723
I'm glad to hear he's doing well.

261
00:13:48,725 --> 00:13:52,237
Since Gyeol doesn't want
other people to know,

262
00:13:53,055 --> 00:13:54,819
please keep it to yourself.

263
00:13:55,749 --> 00:13:58,045
I already told Mr. Ju
to keep his mouth shut too.

264
00:13:59,001 --> 00:14:01,896
I understand what you mean.

265
00:14:03,277 --> 00:14:06,032
Mother,
you're already back from Gyeol's place?

266
00:14:06,236 --> 00:14:08,275
Yes. Where did you go?

267
00:14:08,742 --> 00:14:09,742
Well,

268
00:14:10,803 --> 00:14:13,903
I've been under a lot of stress lately.

269
00:14:14,793 --> 00:14:17,984
And there's nothing better than shopping
to relieve stress.

270
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:21,805
Mother, when you visited Gyeol's place,

271
00:14:22,037 --> 00:14:23,813
didn't you notice anything?

272
00:14:24,123 --> 00:14:25,923
- Notice?
- Signs of a woman.

273
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:29,445
You know, women's clothes,

274
00:14:29,445 --> 00:14:31,789
long strands of hair, matching pajamas...

275
00:14:32,351 --> 00:14:34,493
Watch what you say in front of Father.

276
00:14:35,178 --> 00:14:36,293
I'm done eating.

277
00:14:40,917 --> 00:14:43,256
Do you think Gyeol moved out
for no reason?

278
00:14:43,644 --> 00:14:46,664
He did it
so he could freely date that girl.

279
00:14:46,859 --> 00:14:50,368
You saw the photos
saved on his computer last time.

280
00:14:50,783 --> 00:14:51,783
The intern from the Planning Office.

281
00:14:52,647 --> 00:14:55,900
Turns out she's Mr. Cho's daughter.

282
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:58,432
Those two are completely smitten
with each other right now.

283
00:14:58,602 --> 00:14:59,602
What?

284
00:15:00,663 --> 00:15:02,063
Did you hear that from him?

285
00:15:03,204 --> 00:15:05,453
Well, not exactly.

286
00:15:05,644 --> 00:15:08,264
Then why are you making such a fuss
when nothing's even confirmed?

287
00:15:08,444 --> 00:15:09,902
I'm not making a fuss.

288
00:15:09,902 --> 00:15:10,902
And besides,

289
00:15:11,825 --> 00:15:14,816
is Gyeol's love life
some kind of spectator sport?

290
00:15:16,569 --> 00:15:18,659
Please try to think like a mother
for once.

291
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,699
Think about why Gyeol...

292
00:15:22,152 --> 00:15:24,269
ended up drifting so far away.

293
00:15:29,532 --> 00:15:32,469
Why am I getting blamed? What did I do?

294
00:15:34,173 --> 00:15:37,323
I think we have enough ideas now
for a companion version of Joy.

295
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,605
How would
the Senior Dating Coach app work?

296
00:15:42,893 --> 00:15:45,059
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, are you listening?

297
00:15:46,201 --> 00:15:47,201
Sorry?

298
00:15:47,823 --> 00:15:49,056
The dating coach app.

299
00:15:50,468 --> 00:15:53,259
Well, that idea isn't fully organized yet.

300
00:15:53,503 --> 00:15:54,653
I'll submit it by tomorrow.

301
00:15:55,471 --> 00:15:56,471
Okay.

302
00:15:56,471 --> 00:15:58,416
You have the statistical data
on profitability organized, right?

303
00:15:58,593 --> 00:16:00,171
- Yes, here it is.
- Okay.

304
00:16:08,392 --> 00:16:09,892
There's no need to be so nervous.

305
00:16:10,389 --> 00:16:13,256
There's something important
I wanted to ask you.

306
00:16:13,757 --> 00:16:15,451
Okay.

307
00:16:16,649 --> 00:16:18,149
And don't tell Team Manager Ko.

308
00:16:18,651 --> 00:16:21,176
He might not like it
if I take up the time of a team member...

309
00:16:21,176 --> 00:16:22,432
who's busy preparing for the competition.

310
00:16:23,049 --> 00:16:24,049
Okay.

311
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:25,300
Then I'll see you after work.

312
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:30,688
What does she want to talk about?

313
00:16:32,848 --> 00:16:34,287
Let's wrap up today's meeting here.

314
00:16:34,287 --> 00:16:36,819
Joy seems to be upgrading smoothly.

315
00:16:37,651 --> 00:16:40,341
Your contribution to the second round
has definitely been significant, Eun Ae.

316
00:16:40,632 --> 00:16:41,865
The meeting ended early too.

317
00:16:42,510 --> 00:16:44,152
Then I'll head out first.

318
00:16:44,571 --> 00:16:46,131
- Good work today.
- See you tomorrow.

319
00:16:46,131 --> 00:16:47,131
Bye.

320
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:53,051
What's wrong? Is something bothering you?

321
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,633
What? Something bothering me?

322
00:16:55,707 --> 00:16:56,840
No, not really.

323
00:16:57,745 --> 00:16:59,978
Then shall we meet at the bus stop
in ten minutes?

324
00:17:01,286 --> 00:17:04,221
You should go home first.
Something came up.

325
00:17:04,471 --> 00:17:06,071
What came up all of a sudden?

326
00:17:06,741 --> 00:17:09,688
Don't tell me you're all dressed up
for a blind date or something.

327
00:17:10,019 --> 00:17:12,397
A blind date? Give me a break.

328
00:17:12,397 --> 00:17:13,397
You go ahead.

329
00:17:26,550 --> 00:17:27,550
I'm home.

330
00:17:28,544 --> 00:17:30,356
Welcome back. Perfect timing.

331
00:17:30,356 --> 00:17:31,356
You're here.

332
00:17:31,629 --> 00:17:34,129
Why are you alone... Where's Eun Ae?

333
00:17:34,755 --> 00:17:36,611
She has something to do,
so she'll be a little late.

334
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:40,612
Really? Right. You know
your grandma stopped by today, right?

335
00:17:40,612 --> 00:17:43,359
Yes, I know.
Is there anything I can help with?

336
00:17:43,359 --> 00:17:45,059
Go upstairs, change your clothes,
and come down.

337
00:17:45,059 --> 00:17:48,563
Your grandmother brought tons of kimchi
and side dishes.

338
00:17:48,563 --> 00:17:50,317
I didn't really do anything.

339
00:17:50,613 --> 00:17:52,387
Okay. I'll be right down.

340
00:17:54,416 --> 00:17:56,851
All these side dishes came
from the chairman's house?

341
00:17:56,851 --> 00:17:58,112
That's right.

342
00:17:58,301 --> 00:18:02,323
That elderly lady is incredibly attached
to her grandson.

343
00:18:02,323 --> 00:18:03,504
But doesn't it seem strange?

344
00:18:03,965 --> 00:18:06,792
Usually when a child moves out,

345
00:18:06,792 --> 00:18:09,792
it's the mother who worries more
than the grandmother, right?

346
00:18:10,144 --> 00:18:13,296
I told you.
The mother in that family is completely...

347
00:18:14,985 --> 00:18:17,413
Bit Na.

348
00:18:18,339 --> 00:18:21,095
You need to eat a lot tonight.

349
00:18:21,095 --> 00:18:23,011
Not just a tiny bit like yesterday.

350
00:18:23,813 --> 00:18:25,313
Okay, Grandma.

351
00:18:26,268 --> 00:18:29,147
Why do you seem so down, Bit Na?

352
00:18:29,473 --> 00:18:32,584
You need to eat well and stay cheerful
at Grandma's house...

353
00:18:33,140 --> 00:18:35,520
so your mom will be happy
when she gets back from her business trip.

354
00:18:38,027 --> 00:18:41,000
Cho Bit Na,
why are you crying all of a sudden?

355
00:18:41,455 --> 00:18:42,893
Do you miss your mom?

356
00:18:45,093 --> 00:18:48,376
Bit Na, your mom will be back soon. Why...

357
00:18:49,019 --> 00:18:51,659
Honey, call Eun Hyeong later...

358
00:18:51,952 --> 00:18:53,776
and tell him to come home
and sleep here tonight.

359
00:18:53,776 --> 00:18:54,992
Bit Na can't go on like this.

360
00:18:55,615 --> 00:18:58,579
Okay. He's probably teaching right now,
so I'll call him a little later.

361
00:18:59,066 --> 00:19:00,274
There. Don't cry.

362
00:19:00,274 --> 00:19:03,117
That's my pretty Bit Na. There.

363
00:19:07,565 --> 00:19:11,632
What's this appointment anyway?
Could it really be a blind date?

364
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:17,993
What? You want me
to tell you everything about Han Ji Hun?

365
00:19:18,693 --> 00:19:21,487
Yes. You've worked on Joy
with him for five years.

366
00:19:21,487 --> 00:19:22,837
You should know him better than anyone.

367
00:19:23,396 --> 00:19:27,749
That's true, but I'm not sure
what exactly you want me to tell you.

368
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:29,395
What I want to know most is...

369
00:19:29,632 --> 00:19:32,368
how much Han Ji Hun contributed
to Joy's development...

370
00:19:32,368 --> 00:19:34,068
and what his actual capabilities are.

371
00:19:35,012 --> 00:19:37,312
I shouldn't be saying this
in front of a member of the opposing team,

372
00:19:37,565 --> 00:19:38,875
but while preparing for this competition,

373
00:19:38,877 --> 00:19:41,504
I've started to seriously question
Han Ji Hun's abilities.

374
00:19:43,396 --> 00:19:46,400
The second round is largely evaluated
on how Joy is utilized.

375
00:19:47,045 --> 00:19:49,957
And from what I've seen,
it's hard to believe Han Ji Hun played...

376
00:19:49,957 --> 00:19:51,580
a key role in Joy's development.

377
00:19:51,580 --> 00:19:53,845
I'm sorry to interrupt,

378
00:19:54,573 --> 00:19:58,464
but I don't think I can answer that.

379
00:19:58,775 --> 00:19:59,775
Sorry?

380
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,684
You know
Han Ji Hun and I are on bad terms...

381
00:20:02,684 --> 00:20:04,355
because of the company acquisition issue.

382
00:20:05,216 --> 00:20:09,437
If I say anything,
it wouldn't be objective.

383
00:20:10,299 --> 00:20:11,896
And now that we're working
on separate teams,

384
00:20:12,299 --> 00:20:15,128
honestly, I don't even know...

385
00:20:15,128 --> 00:20:17,547
how far Han Ji Hun's abilities
have progressed.

386
00:20:17,768 --> 00:20:21,469
I feel like I've put you
in an uncomfortable position.

387
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:23,267
Yes, honestly,

388
00:20:23,873 --> 00:20:26,053
it isn't a comfortable question.

389
00:20:27,955 --> 00:20:30,533
Well, if it's difficult for you to answer,
there's nothing I can do.

390
00:20:31,180 --> 00:20:33,861
I'm sorry, Manager. Then I'll...

391
00:20:34,645 --> 00:20:35,645
Wait.

392
00:20:35,787 --> 00:20:38,656
I took up a lot of your time,
so let me drive you home.

393
00:20:39,024 --> 00:20:42,403
What? No, that's okay.
I can just take the bus.

394
00:20:42,672 --> 00:20:45,213
I'm heading home anyway. Don't say no.

395
00:20:45,507 --> 00:20:46,837
Otherwise, I'll feel terrible.

396
00:20:48,291 --> 00:20:49,933
- Let's go together.
- Wait...

397
00:21:04,288 --> 00:21:05,555
Why are the two of them together?

398
00:21:08,188 --> 00:21:10,912
Wait, so Mother went to Gyeol's place?

399
00:21:11,363 --> 00:21:13,701
That's what I'm saying.
She packed up all kinds of food...

400
00:21:13,701 --> 00:21:16,101
to give to the landlord's family.

401
00:21:16,904 --> 00:21:18,784
I mean,
Gyeol isn't even her biological grandson.

402
00:21:18,784 --> 00:21:20,851
I don't know why she's so devoted to him.

403
00:21:21,856 --> 00:21:24,389
Maybe Gyeol is her weak spot.

404
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,560
Don't even get me started.

405
00:21:26,864 --> 00:21:29,464
She practically scolded me today,
telling me to be a proper mother.

406
00:21:31,115 --> 00:21:32,419
Enough with the nonsense.

407
00:21:32,869 --> 00:21:36,864
Crystal, we just need to focus
on opening that safe.

408
00:21:37,459 --> 00:21:39,349
Right, the safe.

409
00:21:39,768 --> 00:21:41,883
This isn't the time for me
to be worrying about other things.

410
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:45,509
Honey, I've got it.

411
00:21:45,969 --> 00:21:47,325
An absolutely brilliant idea.

412
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,200
What is it?

413
00:21:49,368 --> 00:21:50,368
A staged robbery.

414
00:21:50,912 --> 00:21:51,945
A staged robbery?

415
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:55,333
We'll make it look like burglars
broke into the house.

416
00:21:55,508 --> 00:21:56,608
Masked robbers.

417
00:21:57,698 --> 00:21:58,765
Masked robbers?

418
00:22:23,541 --> 00:22:24,811
Who's there?

419
00:22:26,709 --> 00:22:27,955
At that moment,

420
00:22:27,955 --> 00:22:29,731
I'll cut the power.

421
00:22:29,731 --> 00:22:31,760
- And you'll grab the entire safe and run.
- Thief!

422
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:32,760
Thief!

423
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:34,387
Thief!

424
00:22:34,387 --> 00:22:37,341
Thief!

425
00:22:38,176 --> 00:22:40,629
Thief!

426
00:22:42,059 --> 00:22:43,059
A thief?

427
00:22:43,331 --> 00:22:46,231
Thief! Thief!

428
00:22:46,868 --> 00:22:48,019
Mother, are you okay?

429
00:22:48,779 --> 00:22:51,979
Meanwhile, I'll go into the room
and buy you time to escape.

430
00:22:53,499 --> 00:22:56,632
We'll just steal the whole safe outright?

431
00:22:56,632 --> 00:22:58,900
Exactly. Then we'll hand it over
to a trustworthy company...

432
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:00,120
and have it forced open.

433
00:23:00,397 --> 00:23:02,597
Everyone at home will think
it was the work of burglars.

434
00:23:04,704 --> 00:23:06,325
Crystal,
that's actually pretty innovative.

435
00:23:08,717 --> 00:23:10,984
But do you think it'll really work?

436
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,013
There's an emergency alarm...

437
00:23:13,816 --> 00:23:15,249
next to Father's bed. An emergency alarm.

438
00:23:18,993 --> 00:23:19,993
Don't move.

439
00:23:21,057 --> 00:23:22,681
Who are you? Get over here.

440
00:23:22,681 --> 00:23:24,624
Hold still, you punk.

441
00:23:24,624 --> 00:23:25,624
Let's have a look.

442
00:23:27,081 --> 00:23:28,081
Lift your head.

443
00:23:29,201 --> 00:23:30,201
"You punk?"

444
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,200
Dad!

445
00:23:33,164 --> 00:23:34,164
No!

446
00:23:34,731 --> 00:23:38,797
I mean, Min Ho may have served
as a cook in the military,

447
00:23:38,797 --> 00:23:40,597
but he was still a Marine.

448
00:23:40,928 --> 00:23:43,477
If he catches you,
something's definitely getting broken.

449
00:23:43,895 --> 00:23:45,779
And if I get crushed,
are you going to take responsibility?

450
00:23:46,399 --> 00:23:48,005
Did my imagination go too far?

451
00:23:48,005 --> 00:23:49,832
Way too far.

452
00:23:50,482 --> 00:23:52,675
Please get a grip, Crystal.

453
00:23:52,990 --> 00:23:54,757
Now, red sun.

454
00:23:56,635 --> 00:23:59,352
I don't know.
Then what are we supposed to do?

455
00:23:59,352 --> 00:24:03,352
We need to open the safe to find out
where Father's remaining shares are going.

456
00:24:04,209 --> 00:24:07,755
So the best solution
is to find Mother's biological daughter.

457
00:24:07,755 --> 00:24:10,138
Then if we can just learn her birthday,
we can...

458
00:24:10,138 --> 00:24:11,138
Wait, but if we find her,

459
00:24:11,571 --> 00:24:14,067
you only get a fraction of a fraction...

460
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,120
So that's not going to work either.

461
00:24:16,515 --> 00:24:20,264
If that idiot Gwon Sik would just talk,
it'd be game over.

462
00:24:20,805 --> 00:24:23,104
He's just too tight-lipped.

463
00:24:24,428 --> 00:24:26,901
What? A matchmaking agency?

464
00:24:27,179 --> 00:24:31,645
Yes. I need to find Seung Ri someone
as soon as possible.

465
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:34,101
I can't keep watching her suffer.

466
00:24:35,183 --> 00:24:37,635
Do you think Seung Ri
will obediently agree to blind dates?

467
00:24:37,784 --> 00:24:40,584
Of course I won't tell her
it's a blind date.

468
00:24:41,685 --> 00:24:44,861
Who knows? Maybe she'll unexpectedly meet
someone wonderful.

469
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:51,019
I don't intend to keep watching her suffer
because of Gyeol.

470
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:52,550
Who does Gyeol like?

471
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:56,901
Don't tell me it's Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

472
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:01,824
Yes. And she likes Gyeol too.

473
00:25:05,221 --> 00:25:08,477
I'm going to make Seung Ri happy,
no matter what.

474
00:25:11,061 --> 00:25:13,613
What is she worrying herself sick
about today...

475
00:25:14,217 --> 00:25:16,147
that she's still not home?

476
00:25:24,260 --> 00:25:27,027
You should head back now.
We're almost there.

477
00:25:27,426 --> 00:25:29,235
I said I'd drive you all the way home.

478
00:25:30,763 --> 00:25:31,863
Where do you live?

479
00:25:33,096 --> 00:25:34,213
Just a little farther.

480
00:25:34,705 --> 00:25:36,485
Thank you for the ride.

481
00:25:37,653 --> 00:25:39,309
Come to think of it,

482
00:25:39,309 --> 00:25:40,979
your parents and my parents
all know each other.

483
00:25:41,557 --> 00:25:45,320
Since we're already here,
should I stop by your house and say hello?

484
00:25:45,739 --> 00:25:47,739
What? My house?

485
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:53,133
(Team Manager Ko Gyeol)

486
00:25:58,867 --> 00:25:59,867
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

487
00:26:06,917 --> 00:26:09,611
You said you had plans.
Your plans were with Manager Seo?

488
00:26:09,917 --> 00:26:12,389
What? Yes...

489
00:26:13,135 --> 00:26:15,168
Manager Seo gave me a ride home.

490
00:26:17,804 --> 00:26:19,471
What are you doing here, Gyeol?

491
00:26:20,976 --> 00:26:22,309
Why are you at Ms. Cho Eun Ae's house?

492
00:26:23,031 --> 00:26:24,031
I live here.

493
00:26:25,695 --> 00:26:29,228
What? What did you just say?

494
00:26:29,549 --> 00:26:30,749
Exactly what you heard.

495
00:26:31,555 --> 00:26:33,055
I live in the same house as Cho Eun Ae.

496
00:26:36,941 --> 00:26:38,067
I'm sorry, Manager.

497
00:26:38,309 --> 00:26:41,059
Team Manager Ko moved in
without knowing this was my house,

498
00:26:41,289 --> 00:26:42,289
and I only found out afterward...

499
00:26:42,473 --> 00:26:44,306
Why are you apologizing, Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

500
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:51,251
Was I supposed to tell you where I live?

501
00:26:52,196 --> 00:26:53,196
Gyeol.

502
00:26:53,582 --> 00:26:54,582
Team Manager.

503
00:26:54,852 --> 00:26:56,585
Considering you came all the way here
this late,

504
00:26:57,401 --> 00:27:00,557
it seems like you already know everything.
Am I wrong?

505
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:03,940
Stop it!

506
00:27:44,933 --> 00:27:47,700
(Our Happy Days)

507
00:27:47,955 --> 00:27:50,173
What did you just say? You got divorced?

508
00:27:50,173 --> 00:27:51,880
Divorced all of a sudden? Why?

509
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:52,912
Let's go to Eun Hyeong's house.

510
00:27:52,912 --> 00:27:54,715
Let's talk things through
with Ji Seon together.

511
00:27:54,715 --> 00:27:57,003
Ji Seon left.

512
00:27:57,157 --> 00:27:58,501
Make some time tonight.

513
00:27:58,501 --> 00:28:01,227
Why?
Because I want to have dinner with you.

514
00:28:01,227 --> 00:28:02,644
Where are you? I'm here already.

515
00:28:02,644 --> 00:28:03,744
What? A blind date?

516
